{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"cling film, rectangular tart tin (36 cm x 12 cm), rolling pin, baking paper, baking beans, refrigerator, oven","id":"r82875","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-08nAvdmrZNo\/XZanPbP_gpI\/AAAAAAAAg8Q\/uI9ehkGiT3wRb6FCMQaXrodFEYmkGWwvwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_8uNd9TXUdxL_aTPV.png","title":"Bakewell Tart","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pastry"},{"content":"150 g plain flour, plus extra for rolling"},{"content":"35 g icing sugar"},{"content":"100 g unsalted butter, cold, diced"},{"content":"1 egg yolk, from medium egg"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"120 g almonds, blanched"},{"content":"65 g unsalted butter, soft"},{"content":"90 g caster sugar"},{"content":"2 large eggs"},{"content":"½ tsp natural almond extract"},{"content":"120 g raspberry jam"},{"content":"1 Tbsp flaked almonds"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"5.9 g","fat":"22.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"32.8 g","calories":"1500 kJ \/ 359 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pastry"},{"content":"Place flour, icing sugar, butter and egg yolk in mixing bowl then mix <b>25 sec\/speed 4<b>. Tip out and bring together into a flattened ball. Wrap in cling film and refrigerate for 30 minutes."},{"content":"On a lightly floured surface, roll out chilled pastry (approx. 3 mm thick). Transfer pastry to a rectangular tart tin (36 cm x 12 cm), pressing well into corners then trim edges with a knife. Cover with cling film and refrigerate for a further 20 minutes. Meanwhile, make filling."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add butter, sugar, eggs and almond extract then cream <b>1 min\/speed 3<b>. Set mixing bowl aside then preheat oven to 190°C."},{"content":"Once pastry shell has chilled, prick base with a fork then line with baking paper and fill with baking beans. Bake blind for 15 minutes (190°C). Remove baking beans and paper and bake for a further 5 minutes (190°C) until lightly golden. Remove from oven and allow to cool. Turn oven down to 160°C."},{"content":"Spread jam over base of pastry case. Spoon almond filling mixture over jam then sprinkle with flaked almonds. Return to oven and bake for 25-35 minutes (160°C) until golden and firm to the touch. Serve warm or cold, cut in slices."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Use homemade raspberry jam for an even better flavour.","Rice or dried lentils can be used in place of ceramic baking beans when blind baking the pastry case in step 5.","This British classic hails from the picturesque village of Bakewell in Derbyshire. The delicious, distinctive combination of almond and jam makes this a wonderful afternoon tea snack. Can also be warmed and served with custard or cream for pudding."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 50m","10 portions"]}